What is SessionStorage

Ans = SessionStorage is a way to store data on the clientâ€™s computer. It allows the user to access the data across the pages of the website.

1) What is the difference between SessionStorage and LocalStorage?
Ans = SessionStorage is destroyed once the user closes the browser whereas LocalStorage stores data with no expiration date.

Methods with explanation
1)setItem() = This method is used to store the data in the storage object.
2)getItem() = This method is used to retrieve the data from the storage object.
3)removeItem() = This method is used to remove the data from the storage object.
4)clear() = This method is used to remove all the data from the storage object.
